          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Primary 11B beam intensity was ~ 1p mu-A, 33.4 MeV."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EDE",
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COINC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The 3He recoils were detected in coincidence",
                "with 3H. Triple coincidence events 3H-3He-n were also",
                "recorded."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "SISD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " 3He telescope assembly was installed at",
                "a distance of 179 mm from the target. It consisted of",
                "four identical dE-E-E telescopes made of the silicon",
                "strip detectors (SSD). The 20-mu-thick SSD with a",
                "sensitive area of 50x50 mm2 was divided into 16 strips,",
                "the second and the third layers were created by the two",
                "identical 1-mm-thick SSDs (60x60 mm2 with 16 strips).",
                "The angular range covered by these 3 telescopes",
                "for the 3He recoil nuclei was extended up to the",
                "range from ~6 to ~24 degrees in the laboratory system.",
                " Tritons originating from 7H were detected using the",
                "setup where the central telescope was placed at a",
                "distance of 323 mm from the target. It consisted of one",
                "1.5-mm-thick double-sided SSD (64x64 mm2, with 32",
                "strips on each side) followed by a square array of 16",
                "CsI(Tl) crystals."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Neutron spectrometer, made of 48 organic",
                "scintillator modules was used."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Primary 11B beam bombarded the 1-mm thick beryllium",
                "production target. The secondary 8He beam with",
                "intensity ~10**5 pps, was focused on the deuterium",
                "gas target. The 4-mm-thick target cell, equipped with",
                "the 6-mu-thick and 25-mm diameter stainless-steel",
                "entrance and exit windows, was cooled down to 27 K",
                "and filled with the deuterium gas up to a pressure at",
                "which the target thickness was ~3.7x10**2 cm(-2)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "PART-DET": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HE3",
                "T"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "EN-SEC": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "E",
                "particle": "1-H-7"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Decay energy above the 3H+4n threshold is",
                "given."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ADD-RES": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "H-2(Be-10,He-3)Li-9 g.s. was studied at 42 A MeV 10Be",
                "secondary beam. The cross-section values of ~7-10 mb/sr",
                "at forward angles in the center-of-mass system were",
                "deduced for the 9Li ground state."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "STRUC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " With obtained 7H spectra the authors assign the",
                "ground state at 2.2(3) MeV, the first excited state at",
                "5.5(3) MeV, and the higher-energy resonances at 7.5(3)",
                "and 11.0(5) MeV."
              ]
            }
          ],
